study_design_info.masking_description:
Computer-generated randomization numbers will be used to randomly assign patients into 3 groups using sealed opaque envelopes that will be randomly selected by each patient and contained a group number in which the patient was enrolled. Once enrolled in the study, patients will be randomly assigned into 3 groups;
Group I (ESP Group): will receive US-guided ESPB. Group II (AQL Group): will receive US-guided AQLB. Group III (Control Group): will receive IV multimodal analgesia only.
Both patients and data collector responsible for assessing outcomes will be blinded to group assignment (double-blinded clinical trial).
